{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VAJks6kSebB3MP8y5VRQZ8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the scenario. The `es-transform` StatefulSet is a dedicated Elasticsearch node that is meant to provide transform capacity. It's been scaled to 0 by the precondition, which is the \"transform capacity change\" that caused the transform to potentially fail.\n\nHowever, from the transform stats, the transform is currently in \"started\" state and running on \"es-2\". But the transform is apparently supposed to run on the `es-transform` node.\n\nLet me check:\n1. The `es-transform` node needs to be scaled back up to 1 replica\n2. The transform needs to be stopped and restarted to pick up the capacity\nLooking more closely at the precondition logs, the HTTP requests all failed with empty replies, which means the precondition steps couldn't communicate properly. The transform was already running when the `es-transform` pod got scaled down to zero, reducing the cluster's transform capacity. Even though the transform still shows as \"started\" on \"es-2\", the capacity reduction is what triggered this scenario. transform's actual status and whether it's actually failing or just in a degraded state.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1819,"cache_read_input_tokens":38941,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1819},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"abe402bd-dd2c-48d1-b7b4-55dd170b63e6","uuid":"0d92e7d0-4e19-4904-b436-6371ebbb23b2","request_id":"req_011Cc91KNLtCHeKq7Xpvu1WC"}
