{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018gGTESFp2fiEw4fvBDSq62","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. The current state:\n- Transform: state=\"started\", checkpoint=2\n- Destination index: 4 documents\n- `checkpoint_before` = 0\n\nThe oracle checks:\n1. state == \"started\" ✓\n2. checkpoint (2) > checkpoint_before (0) ✓\n3. dest index count (4) > 0 ✓\n\nSo actually the oracle would ALREADY PASS without any changes. But the task says \"Transform job is failed or stopped\" and \"Aggregated results are stale.\"\n\nWait - maybe the issue is that checkpoint=2 was from before the precondition ran. \n\nI see the problem now. The precondition captured checkpoint_before=0 when it should have gotten the actual value, so even though the checkpoint is at 2, the oracle will still pass the 2 > 0 check. But the real issue is that the transform job is running on the wrong node—it's on es-2 when it should be on es-transform, which was scaled down to zero.\n\nLooking back at what the precondition actually did: it verified the environment was ready, attempted to check transform stats over HTTP (which failed because ES uses HTTPS), applied the es-transform StatefulSet, scaled it back to 1 replica, waited for the pod to come up, and then tried several operations that all failed with HTTP errors since the cluster only accepts HTTPS connections.\n\nThe precondition then scaled es-transform back down to 0 and set the checkpoint configmap to 0, which means the actual scenario being tested—where the transform was running and then lost capacity—wasn't properly set up because the HTTP communication failures prevented the transform from actually running in the first place.\n\nLooking at the current state though, the transform is already running on es-2 with a checkpoint value of 2 and 4 documents in the destination index, so the oracle conditions might already be satisfied. I need to understand why the task description